---
// A/B Test Entry Page
// Redirects to V1, V2, or V3 based on variant assignment
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Validation Landing Pages - A/B Test</title>
  
  <style>
    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }

    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', 'Roboto', sans-serif;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2C5F2D 0%, #1e4620 100%);
      color: white;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-height: 100vh;
      padding: 2rem;
    }

    .loader-container {
      text-align: center;
      max-width: 500px;
    }

    .spinner {
      width: 50px;
      height: 50px;
      border: 4px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
      border-top-color: white;
      border-radius: 50%;
      animation: spin 1s linear infinite;
      margin: 0 auto 2rem;
    }

    @keyframes spin {
      to { transform: rotate(360deg); }
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    p {
      opacity: 0.9;
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .debug-info {
      margin-top: 2rem;
      padding: 1rem;
      background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
      border-radius: 8px;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      text-align: left;
    }

    .debug-info code {
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
      padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    }

    noscript {
      display: block;
      padding: 2rem;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
      border-radius: 8px;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }

    noscript a {
      color: white;
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="loader-container">
    <div class="spinner"></div>
    <h1>Assigning your validation page variant...</h1>
    <p>
      You're being assigned to one of three page variants for our A/B test. 
      This helps us understand which approach works best for founders like you.
    </p>
    
    <div class="debug-info">
      <strong>A/B Test Setup:</strong><br>
      • 50% → V3 (Comprehensive + Authentic)<br>
      • 25% → V1 (Simplified Professional)<br>
      • 25% → V2 (Simplified Problem-Focused)<br><br>
      
      <strong>Debug:</strong> Open console to see assignment details<br>
      <code>window.variantTest.info()</code> - View current variant<br>
      <code>window.variantTest.clearVariant()</code> - Reset variant<br>
      <code>window.variantTest.setVariant('v1')</code> - Force variant
    </div>

    <noscript>
      <p>
        <strong>JavaScript is disabled.</strong><br>
        Please enable JavaScript or visit directly:<br><br>
        <a href="/validate/">V1 - Simplified Professional</a><br>
        <a href="/validate-v2/">V2 - Simplified Problem-Focused</a><br>
        <a href="/validate-v3/">V3 - Comprehensive</a>
      </p>
    </noscript>
  </div>

  <!-- Load variant assignment script -->
  <script src="/js/variant-assignment.js"></script>
</body>
</html>


